    {
      "instruction": "<p>Boil a kettle and heat a large, wide-based pot with a drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil</strong> over a medium heat</p><p>Once hot, add the <strong>chicken</strong> <strong>breasts</strong> and cook for 3 min on each side</p><p>Remove the pot from the heat, then add 300ml <span class=\"text-danger\">[500ml]</span> <strong>boiled water</strong>, the <strong>chicken stock mix</strong> and <strong>half</strong> the <strong>soy sauce</strong> (you’ll use the rest later!)</p><p>Return the pot to a medium-low heat and cook, covered, for 10 min or until the chicken is cooked through (no pink meat!)</p>",
      "order": 2,
      "media": {
        "images": [
